---
# Overrides for the standalone example programs. These are demonstrations meant to be read
# and run, not library code, and they extend rather than replace the repository-root config.
#
#   * `misc-misleading-bidirectional` -- bidi-demo.cpp exists to demonstrate bidirectional
#     text, and it frames its reference renderings in U+202D LEFT-TO-RIGHT OVERRIDE ...
#     U+202C POP DIRECTIONAL FORMAT so that a terminal which has implemented BiDi does not
#     reorder the already-reordered reference and make a correct terminal look broken.
#     The check reads the *value* of a string literal rather than its spelling, so writing
#     the controls as \u202D / \u202C escapes -- which the file does, to keep invisible
#     characters out of the source -- does not and cannot satisfy it. The check guards
#     against Trojan Source (CVE-2021-42574), where bidi controls make code read
#     differently than it compiles; a literal deliberately emitting one to the terminal is
#     the legitimate case it cannot distinguish.
InheritParentConfig: true
Checks: >-
  -misc-misleading-bidirectional
